http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/kerala/Church-consecration-today/article14012893.ece

The newly constructed Saint Antony’s Thekkemuri parish church in East Kallada will be consecrated by Kollam Bishop Stanley Roman at 3 p.m. on January 22.A holy relic of Saint Antony, which will be preserved at the church, will be brought by the faithful in a procession starting from the Saint Antony’s shrine at Kundara Mukkada at 12 noon.The cultural gathering at the church compound after the consecration ritual will be inaugurated by Leader of the Opposition V.S. Achuthanandan.Swamy Sandeepanandagiri, Imam Ashraf Maulavi, and Fr. Abraham Thalothil will deliver the benedictory addresses on the occasion.